\v 11 On that day the number of those that were slain in Shushan the palace
was brought before the king.
\p
\v 12 And the king said unto Esther the queen, The Jews have slain and
destroyed five hundred men in Shushan the palace, and the ten sons of Haman;
what have they done in the rest of the king’s provinces? now what \add is
\add* thy petition? and it shall be granted thee: or what \add is\add* thy
request further? and it shall be done. 
\v 13 Then said Esther, If it please the king, let it be granted to the Jews
