decree, and let Haman’s ten sons be hanged upon the gallows. 
\v 14 And the king commanded it so to be done: and the decree was given at
Shushan; and they hanged Haman’s ten sons. 
\v 15 For the Jews that \add were\add* in Shushan gathered themselves together
on the fourteenth day also of the month Adar, and slew three hundred men at
Shushan; but on the prey they laid not their hand. 
\v 16 But the other Jews that \add were\add* in the king’s provinces gathered
themselves together, and stood for their lives, and had rest from their
enemies, and slew of their foes seventy and five thousand, but they laid not
their hands on the prey, 
\v 17 On the thirteenth day of the month Adar; and on the fourteenth day of
the same rested they, and made it a day of feasting and gladness. 
\v 18 But the Jews that \add were\add* at Shushan assembled together on the
thirteenth \add day\add* thereof; and on the fourteenth thereof; and on the
fifteenth \add day\add* of the same they rested, and made it a day of feasting
and gladness. 
\v 19 Therefore the Jews of the villages, that dwelt in the unwalled towns,
made the fourteenth day of the month Adar \add a day of\add* gladness and
